Death during an elective surgical procedure","Death from acute myocardial infarction in hospital"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Edeath during an elective surgical procedure\u003C/strong\u003E must be reported to the coroner as it is considered a death that may have resulted from a medical procedure. This allows investigation of the circumstances and determination if the death was preventable.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe following deaths do not require mandatory reporting:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDeath from pneumonia in a nursing home resident\u003C/strong\u003E represents a natural death with a clear medical cause.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDeath from advanced metastatic cancer under palliative care\u003C/strong\u003E represents an expected death from natural causes with a clear medical diagnosis.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDeath from end-stage renal failure on dialysis\u003C/strong\u003E is an expected death from a known chronic medical condition.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDeath from acute myocardial infarction in hospital\u003C/strong\u003E is considered a natural cause of death with a clear diagnosis, despite being sudden.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOther deaths that must be reported to the coroner include those resulting from accidents, suicide, violence, unknown causes, deaths in custody, and deaths where the person\u0027s identity is unknown.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A reportable death requires notification to the coroner for investigation of unexpected, unnatural, or violent circumstances.","Healthcare workers have a legal obligation to report deaths that fall under coroner jurisdiction.","Deaths from medical procedures, accidents, suicide, and unknown causes must be reported to the coroner."],"references":["Information for health professionals. Coroners Court of Queensland. Updated November 2022. Available from: https://www.coronerscourt.qld.gov.au/__data/assets/pdf_file/0008/785573/information-for-health-professionals.pdf","Mandal J, Ponnambath DK, Parija SC. Bioethics: A brief review. Trop Parasitol. 2017;7(1):5-7. doi:10.4103/tp.TP_4_17","Varkey B. Principles of Clinical Ethics and Their Application to Practice. Med Princ Pract. 2021;30(1):17-28. doi:10.1159/000509119"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60681"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17834"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60681","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60681"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-29T09:10:40+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-29T09:11:10+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10548"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75173"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"hea